      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It's clear that your sense of identity and purpose has been deeply tied to your work, and the loss of that validation can be devastating. Losing one's sense of self can be a profoundly isolating experience. It's okay to acknowledge your feelings and take time to grieve the loss of your former identity, but try not to take it as a permanent truth. You are more than your work, and it's possible to rediscover your sense of purpose and self-worth beyond this one area.",
      "source": "target",
